tldr: The user requested a thorough review of a recently implemented interactive
  sleep questionnaire and its associated database and API endpoints. The goal is
  to ensure all acceptance criteria are met for this freemium tool, which
  provides personalized sleep health guidance or probable sleep disorder
  diagnoses based on user input.
overview: The user's intent was to have a comprehensive review of a recently
  implemented interactive sleep questionnaire, its database, and API endpoints.
  The project, named "Somna Health Practical Sleep Questionnaire," aims to be a
  smart, patient-interactive tool based on psychometrically validated items.
  It's designed as a freemium service, collecting only de-identified demographic
  data (year of birth, zipcode/county, sex) while capturing raw, de-identified
  data. Functionally, it will either guide users toward sleep health
  optimization or provide probable diagnoses for various sleep disorders (e.g.,
  Insomnia, OSA, Narcolepsy) with recommendations for further information and
  treatment. The approach involves a web-based application with branching logic,
  narrative report generation (including PDF download), and a database for
  response storage with CSV retrieval. The Statement of Work outlines the scope,
  responsibilities, timeline, and fees for the development by Helvetica Lake.
  The user provided a detailed questionnaire structure with "IF Formulas" and
  "Messages" to guide the review.
